==English==
===Adjective===
{{wikipediaAlt|Caucasian race}}
[[Category:English adjectives]]
'''Caucasian'''
#(''anthropology'') of a [[human]] [[racial]] [[classification]]; including [[people]]s of [[Europe]], [[Northern]] [[Africa]], [[Western]] [[Asia]], [[Southern Asia]] and parts of [[Central Asia]] having very light to brown pigmented skin.
#of, or relating to the [[Caucasus]] [[region]] or its [[people]], [[language]]s and [[culture]]
===Proper noun===
[[Category:English proper nouns]]
'''Caucasian'''
#(''anthropology, archaic'') a member of the Caucasian racial classification
#a [[native]] or [[inhabitant]] of the Caucasus

===Noun===
[[Category:English nouns]]
'''Caucasian'''
#(''linguistics'') a group of languages spoken in the [[Caucasus]] area
#(''bartending'') a humourous name for the [[White Russian]], a cocktail consisting of coffee liqueur, vodka, and milk


